<section xml:id="C28.S4">
<title>Fourier Series</title>        
  
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS1">
<title>Definitions</title>        
 
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C28.S4.SS1.p1.s1">
The Fourier series of the periodic Mathieu functions converge absolutely and uniformly on all compact sets in the <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS1.p1.m1">z</Math> -plane.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C28.S4.SS1.p1.s2">
For <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS1.p1.m2">n=0,1,2,3,\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.1" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E1">\mathrm{ce}_{2n}\left(z,q\right)=\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}A^{2n}_{2m}(q)\cos 2mz,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.2" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E2">\mathrm{ce}_{2n+1}\left(z,q\right)=\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}A^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)\cos(2 m+1)z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.3" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E3">\mathrm{se}_{2n+1}\left(z,q\right)=\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}B^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)\sin(2 m+1)z,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.4" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E4">\mathrm{se}_{2n+2}\left(z,q\right)=\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}B^{2n+2}_{2m+2}(q)\sin(2 m+2)z</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS2">
<title>Recurrence Relations</title>        
   
  
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C28.S4.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.4.5" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E5">aA_{0}-qA_{2}=0,(a-4)A_{2}-q(2A_{0}+A_{4})=0,(a-4m^{2})A_{2m}-q(A_{2m-2}+A_{2m+2})=0, , if m=2,3,4,\dots, a=a_{2n}\left(q\right), A_{2m}=A_{2m}^{2n}(q)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C28.S4.SS2.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="28.4.6" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E6">(a-1-q)A_{1}-qA_{3}=0,\left(a-(2m+1)^{2}\right)A_{2m+1}-q(A_{2m-1}+A_{2m+3})=0, , if m=1,2,3,\dots, a=a_{2n+1}\left(q\right), A_{2m+1}=A_{2m+1}^{2n+1}(q)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C28.S4.SS2.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="28.4.7" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E7">(a-1+q)B_{1}-qB_{3}=0,\left(a-(2m+1)^{2}\right)B_{2m+1}-q(B_{2m-1}+B_{2m+3})=0, , if m=1,2,3,\dots, a=b_{2n+1}\left(q\right), B_{2m+1}=B_{2m+1}^{2n+1}(q)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C28.S4.SS2.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="28.4.8" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E8">(a-4)B_{2}-qB_{4}=0,(a-4m^{2})B_{2m}-q(B_{2m-2}+B_{2m+2})=0, , if m=2,3,4,\dots, a=b_{2n+2}\left(q\right), B_{2m+2}=B_{2m+2}^{2n+2}(q)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS3">
<title>Normalization</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS3.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C28.S4.SS3.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.4.9" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E9">2\left(A^{2n}_{0}(q)\right)^{2}+\sum_{m=1}^{\infty}\left(A^{2n}_{2m}(q)\right) ^{2}=1,</Math> <Math equation-number="28.4.10" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E10">\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}\left(A^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)\right)^{2}=1,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.11" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E11">\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}\left(B^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)\right)^{2}=1,</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.12" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E12">\sum_{m=0}^{\infty}\left(B^{2n+2}_{2m+2}(q)\right)^{2}=1</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C28.S4.SS3.p1.s2">
Ambiguities in sign are resolved by (28.4.13)–(28.4.16) when <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS3.p1.m1">q=0</Math> , and by continuity for the other values of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS3.p1.m2">q</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS4">
<title>Case <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS4.m1">q=0</Math></title>        
 
 
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C28.S4.SS4.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.4.13" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E13">A^{0}_{0}(0)=1/\sqrt{2},\quad A^{2n}_{2n}(0)=1, if n&gt;0, //// A^{2n}_{2m}(0)=0, if n\neq m,</Math> <Math equation-number="28.4.14" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E14">A^{2n+1}_{2n+1}(0)=1,A^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(0)=0, if n\neq m,</Math> <Math equation-number="28.4.15" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E15">B^{2n+1}_{2n+1}(0)=1,B^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(0)=0, if n\neq m,</Math> <Math equation-number="28.4.16" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E16">B^{2n+2}_{2n+2}(0)=1,B^{2n+2}_{2m+2}(0)=0, if n\neq m</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS5">
<title>Change of Sign of <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS5.m1">q</Math></title>          
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS5.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C28.S4.SS5.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="28.4.17" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E17">A^{2n}_{2m}(-q)=(-1)^{n-m}A^{2n}_{2m}(q),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.18" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E18">B^{2n+2}_{2m+2}(-q)=(-1)^{n-m}B^{2n+2}_{2m+2}(q),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.19" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E19">A^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(-q)=(-1)^{n-m}B^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q),</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.20" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E20">B^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(-q)=(-1)^{n-m}A^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS6">
<title>Behavior for Small <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.m1">q</Math></title>        
  
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p1.s1">
For fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p1.m1">s=1,2,3,\dots</Math> and fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p1.m2">m=1,2,3,\dots</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.21" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E21">A^{0}_{2s}(q)=\left(\dfrac{(-1)^{s}2}{(s!)^{2}}\left(\frac{q}{4}\right)^{s}+O \left(q^{s+2}\right)\right)A^{0}_{0}(q),</Math> <Math equation-number="28.4.22" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E22">\rselection{A^{m}_{m+2s}(q)\\ B^{m}_{m+2s}(q)}=\left(\dfrac{(-1)^{s}m!}{s!(m+s)!}\left(\frac{q}{4}\right)^{s }+O\left(q^{s+1}\right)\right)\lselection{A^{m}_{m}(q),\\ B^{m}_{m}(q),}</Math> <Math equation-number="28.4.23" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E23">\rselection{A^{m}_{m-2s}(q)\\ B^{m}_{m-2s}(q)}=\left(\dfrac{(m-s-1)!}{s!(m-1)!}\left(\frac{q}{4}\right)^{s}+ O\left(q^{s+1}\right)\right)\lselection{A^{m}_{m}(q),\\ B^{m}_{m}(q).</Math>
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p1.s2">
}
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C28.S4.SS6.p2.s1">
For further terms and expansions see Meixner and Schäfke (1954, p. 122) and McLachlan (1947, §3.33).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C28.S4.SS7">
<title>Asymptotic Forms for Large <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.m1">m</Math></title>        
  
<para xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="14" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.s1">
As <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.m1">m\to\infty</Math> , with fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.m2">q</Math> ( <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.m3">\neq 0</Math> ) and fixed <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.m4">n</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.24" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E24">\frac{A^{2n}_{2m}(q)}{A^{2n}_{0}(q)}=\frac{(-1)^{m}}{(m!)^{2}}\left(\frac{q}{4 }\right)^{m}\frac{\pi\left(1+O\left(m^{-1}\right)\right)}{w_{\mbox{\tiny II}}( \frac{1}{2}\pi;a_{2n}\left(q\right),q)},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.25" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E25">\frac{A^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)}{A^{2n+1}_{1}(q)}=\frac{(-1)^{m+1}}{\left({\left( \tfrac{1}{2}\right)_{m+1}}\right)^{2}}\left(\frac{q}{4}\right)^{m+1}\frac{2 \left(1+O\left(m^{-1}\right)\right)}{w^{\prime}_{\mbox{\tiny II}}(\frac{1}{2} \pi;a_{2n+1}\left(q\right),q)},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.26" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E26">\frac{B^{2n+1}_{2m+1}(q)}{B^{2n+1}_{1}(q)}=\frac{(-1)^{m}}{\left({\left(\tfrac {1}{2}\right)_{m+1}}\right)^{2}}\left(\frac{q}{4}\right)^{m+1}\frac{2\left(1+O \left(m^{-1}\right)\right)}{w_{\mbox{\tiny I}}(\frac{1}{2}\pi;b_{2n+1}\left(q \right),q)},</Math> , <Math equation-number="28.4.27" mode="display" xml:id="C28.S4.E27">\frac{B^{2n+2}_{2m}(q)}{B^{2n+2}_{2}(q)}=\frac{(-1)^{m}}{(m!)^{2}}\left(\frac{ q}{4}\right)^{m}\frac{q\pi\left(1+O\left(m^{-1}\right)\right)}{w^{\prime}_{ \mbox{\tiny I}}(\frac{1}{2}\pi;b_{2n+2}\left(q\right),q)}</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="15" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.s2">
For the basic solutions <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.m5">w_{\mbox{\tiny I}}</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C28.S4.SS7.p1.m6">w_{\mbox{\tiny II}}</Math> see §28.2(ii).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
</section>
